          "correctOptionId": "opt-2",
          "explanation": "Ans:C i.e. The laryngoscope is lifted upward levering over the upper incisiors. Procedure of Endotracheal Intubation: The correct position is with the lower pa of the cervical spine flexed (by placing a pillow or other suitable pad under the patient's occiput), and the atlanto-occipital joint extended(by tilting the head back) - the so-called \"sniffing position\". This position aligns the axes of the mouth, pharynx and trachea, and will give the best visualization of the cords during laryngoscopy. In a Straight Blade Laryngoscope,lift the epiglottis with the tip of the blade."
