          "explanation": "Answer: c) ProprioceptionProprioception is the first sensation to recover from anesthesia.It is followed by muscle tone, pain, touch, and temperature.The order of sensitivity is of nerve fibers to anesthetic is:Type B and C > type A d > type Ab and Ag > type AaThinner and myelinated fibers have greater firing range and are the first nerve fibers to be affected during anesthesia.",
