          "correctOptionId": "opt-1",
          "explanation": "Answer: a) Tetanic tension is poorNon-depolarizing muscle relaxants act as pharmacological antagonists at the skeletal muscle end-plate.It acts by competitive antagonism.These agents show post-tetanic potentiation, while the tetanic tension declines rapidly.Response to the tetanic stimulus is unsustained with non-depolarizing muscle relaxants, whereas it is sustained during phase I block with depolarizing muscle relaxants.",
