          "explanation": "A stellate ganglion block is an injection of local anesthetic in the sympathetic nerve tissue of the neck. These nerves are a pa of the sympathetic nervous system. The nerves are located on either side of the voice box, in the neck.",
          "hint": "Topic: Fundamental concepts"
