          "correctOptionId": "opt-3",
          "explanation": "A sudden drop of ET Co2 to near Zero followed by absence of a Co2 waveform heralds a potentially life threatening problem. Differential diagnosis D/d. 1. Malposition of an Endotracheal tube into the pharynx or oesophagus. 2. Circuit Disconnection 3. Stoppage of ventilation 4. Cardiac arrest 5. Massive pulmonary embolism",
