          "explanation": "Sevoflurane REF: Morgan's anesthesia 3\" ed p. 404, 570, 860, 884 \"Sevoflurane is anesthetic of choice for induction in pediatrics because of rapid onset and non-pungency\" Induction in pediatrics patient Inhalation -- Sevoflurane in N20 Intravenous (preferred) - rapid acting barbiturate like thiopental or Propofol followed by non-depolarizing muscle relaxant. Intramuscular- Ketamine Muscle relaxant (MR)- Rocuronium"
