          "explanation": "Ester local anesthetics (like procaine & tetracaine) are metabolized by cholinesterase (pseudocholinesterase). Amide local anesthetics (Bupivacaine) are metabolized in liver (not by pseudocholinesterase).\nAcetylcholine is metabolized by cholinesterase (acetylcholinesterase)."
