          "correctOptionId": "opt-1",
          "explanation": "Monitoring of Neuromuscular block Done by nerve stimulator Different stimulation - Single Twitch Tetanus Train of four stimulus (most common) Double burst stimulation Post - tetanic count Nerves used - ulnar nerve (most common) (Adductor pollicis muscle ) Facial nerve Posterior tibial nerve External peroneal nerve Response of stimulation",
