          "correctOptionId": "opt-1",
          "explanation": "Low pressure - high volume type cuffs have a comparatively large volumes and consequently large contact areas between cuff and trachea. Advantage of high volume, low pressure cuff is lesser incidence of tracheal mucosal damage. Disadvantages of high volume, low pressure cuff include: Sore throat (due to larger mucosal contact area) Aspiration Spontaneous extubation Difficulty in inseion (because of the floppy cuff)",
